---

<section style="padding:5rem 0;">
  <div style="max-width:780px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 1.5rem;">

    <!-- Eyebrow -->
    <p class="fade-in" style="font-family:'Jost',system-ui,sans-serif;font-size:10px;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.28em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#c9a84c;margin:0 0 1.25rem;text-align:center;">
      The hook
    </p>

    <!-- H2 -->
    <h2 class="fade-in" style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif;font-weight:500;font-size:clamp(2rem,6vw,3rem);line-height:1.08;letter-spacing:-0.01em;color:#f0ebe0;margin:0 0 2rem;text-align:center;">
      Your friends can make it <em style="color:#c9a84c;font-style:italic;">harder.</em>
    </h2>

    <!-- Body -->
    <div class="fade-in" style="font-family:'Jost',system-ui,sans-serif;font-weight:300;font-size:1rem;line-height:1.75;color:#a39e92;max-width:600px;margin:0 auto 2.5rem;">
      <p style="margin:0 0 1.25em;">
        Every morning you draw five cards across Physical, Mental, Nutrition, Recovery, and Wildcard. You commit to two or three.
      </p>
      <p style="margin:0 0 1.25em;">
        What you commit to is locked. No one touches it — not while you're working, not after you've finished. Your cards are yours.
      </p>
      <p style="margin:0;">
        What your friends can reach is tomorrow's draw. Before you wake up, they can spend a vault card on you. A harder card swaps into the hand. A commitment waits for you before you've seen the rest. The whole draw goes dark and you choose blind. Or they leave you something better.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Pull-quote -->
    <div style="display:flex;justify-content:center;">
      <blockquote
        class="fade-in"
        style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',Georgia,serif;font-style:italic;font-size:clamp(1.4rem,3.5vw,1.8rem);line-height:1.4;color:#c9a84c;border-left:2px solid #c9a84c;padding-left:1.5rem;margin:0;max-width:500px;"
      >
        "Completed cards are immune. That's the deal."
      </blockquote>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
